'''Osteomyelitis of the jaws''' is [[osteomyelitis]] ([[inflammation]] of the [[bone marrow]]) which occurs in the bones of the jaws (i.e. [[maxilla]] or the [[human mandible|mandible]]). Historically, osteomyelitis of the jaws was a common complication of infections of the teeth. Before the antibiotic era, it was frequently a fatal condition.<ref name="Peravali 2011">{{cite journal|last=Peravali|first=Ranjit Kumar|coauthors=Jayade, Bhushan; Joshi, Abhijit; Shirganvi, Mahantesh; Bhasker Rao, C.; Gopalkrishnan, K.|title=Osteomyelitis of Maxilla in Poorly Controlled Diabetics in a Rural Indian Population|journal=Journal of Maxillofacial and Oral Surgery|date=1 October 2011|volume=11|issue=1|pages=57<U+2013>66|doi=10.1007/s12663-011-0283-0|pmid=23449555}}</ref> 

